# CLAUDE.md — annotated template

<!--
  This is a template for the CLAUDE.md file at your repo root: the onboarding
  document Claude Code (and any agent) reads at session start.

  HTML comments like this one are annotations explaining what each section is
  FOR — delete them when adapting. Everything else is skeleton to fill in.

  The one test for every line you keep: "has its absence ever caused a bad
  diff?" If not, cut it. Context files get skimmed when bloated — by agents
  and humans alike.

  A real, production example of this structure (public):
  https://github.com/TIP-Global-Health/eheza-app/blob/main/CLAUDE.md
-->

