## Code Conventions

<!--
  ONLY the rules a reviewer would actually flag — the ones that bite. Each
  convention: what to do, and (in one clause) why, so the agent can apply it
  to unforeseen cases. Aim for 3–7 conventions, not 30.

  Real examples of the genre (from the linked production file):
  - "Union type variants, case branches, and pattern matches must be in
    alphabetical order" — mechanical, reviewable, prevents merge noise.
  - "When a translation would be identical to English, leave it as Nothing —
    it falls back at runtime" — encodes a runtime behavior the agent can't
    guess from types.
  - "Do not include Debug.log calls in commits."
  - "Always append [ci skip] to commit messages unless asked to run CI" —
    saves a paid CI run per WIP commit.
-->

